source.name: Latest Volumes of Foreign Relations of the United States
source.description: The Office of the Historian is responsible, under law, for the preparation and publication of the official historical documentary record of U.S. foreign policy in the Foreign Relations of the United States series.  The dataset that the Office of the Historian is submitting is the feed for the latest ten volumes in the series.  Each record in the dataset contains a volume's title, year of publication, summary, and link to the online volumes. The feed will update when current volumes are edited or new volumes are published.
